# Update Logging

- Keep project progress in `UPDATE_LOG/` using GitHub-renderable markdown.
- Keep exactly one daily log file named `YYYY-MM-DD_summary.md` for each day of work.
- Treat `UPDATE_LOG/2026-03-28_000000_initial-plan.md` as the one special standalone initial log entry.
- Append new sections to the current day's file instead of creating multiple files for the same day.
- Review the current daily log filename summary on each update and rename the file if the day's scope has changed enough that the summary is no longer accurate.
- If the user explicitly describes manual edits or decisions, record them as human updates in the relevant log entry.
- Keep dialog summaries short and simplified.
- Maintain `UPDATE_LOG/README.md` as an index sorted newest day first, with the initial log listed separately.
- Do not duplicate unchanged details across many entries; link or summarize instead.
